The ID of the form template version that this data corresponds to.

signatureFields.description: The names of the form fields on this form that are mapped to signatures.

createdOn.description: When the form field was created.

updatedOn.description: When the form field was last modified.

associatedObjectDefinitionId.description: The Associated Object Definition Id that this field should get its data from. This will be null if the field belongs to a list.

calculationParameters.description: The calculation parameters, these vary depending on the calculation operation.

checkComparator.description: Only used for checkbox fields. The value that makes the checkbox checked on the form.

filterPath.description: The path of the property on the object that should be used in the filter.

filterReferenceField.description: The ID of the field that this filter should reference. Only used for certain filter operations.

filterValue.description: The filter value, this varies depending on the filter operation.

formListId.description: The id of the Form List that this form field belongs to. This will be null if this field does not belong to a list.

id.description: Unique ID of the form field.

listIndex.description: If this field belongs to a Form List or points to a list property on the object, this is which item in the list it should get its data from. If the list is grouped, this references the index of the key and it will always get the first item in the list that belongs to that key. (0 = none)

mapToSignature.description: Whether or not this form field should be mapped to a signature.

name.description: The name of the form field.

overflowFormTemplateVersionId.description: The Form Template Version Id of the overflow form that this field should overflow to.

overflowPriority.description: The priority in which this field will overflow. A lower number will overflow first. If not supplied, overflow order is not guaranteed.

overrideDefault.description: Whether this form field's values should override the defaults when published

path.description: The path to the property on the object. Used to get the value to populate the field.

startAtOverflowPoint.description: Whether or not the value of this field should start at the point which it overflowed from a parent form.

textLimit.description: The maximum number of characters that can fit in this form field. Only used to determine if this field should overflow. (0 = none)

type.description: The type of the form field.

documentPath.description: Document path to be used. Must specify a file extension

notes.description: Notes for this form instance. Maximum 500 characters.

unmappedFieldData.description: List of unmapped field data. Must be in the same order as mapped data.

limit.description: The number of items that this list can hold.
